      "side": 1,
      "message": "It\u0027s EGL_CONTEXT_OPENGL_PROFILE_MASK_KHR of https://www.khronos.org/registry/EGL/extensions/KHR/EGL_KHR_create_context.txt, a way for desktop GL to integrate with EGL (ES doesn\u0027t care about this), to set the compatibility or core profile property of a new context.\n\nSince OpenGL ES doesn\u0027t care about this, we can steal it for configuring the host-side GL to use core profile, from RenderControl, directly vs pulling in libOpenglRender again in the EGL translator (Thank you and Yahan for pushing on it)",
